# IBKR Execution Refactor Checklist

Use this when refactoring any IBKR execution code for production use.

## Goals
- Reduce latency on hot paths.
- Reduce API chatter.
- Eliminate duplicate-order risk.
- Separate signal logic from broker execution.
- Make startup reconciliation mandatory.
- Cache contract metadata and market rules.
- Minimize order modification churn.
- Preserve deterministic order state transitions.

## Constraints
- Use typed domain models.
- No hidden globals.
- No repeated contract resolution if cached.
- No polling if broker callbacks/events can drive state.
- No DataFrame-heavy logic in live execution paths.
- All retries must be bounded and idempotent.
- All broker interactions must be structured-logged.

## Required Output (in this order)
1. Architecture changes
2. Failure modes
3. Refactored code
4. Tests
5. Remaining risks
